{"sequence":60,"timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:38:09.205541715Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-7a1032e2","body":"`src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:749-752` still deletes `run.pid` whenever `mark_running_run_interrupted()` rereads a non-`Running` snapshot. That reintroduces the same startup-window bug this patch was trying to close: stale recovery is triggered before the writer lease is reacquired (`src/cli/run.rs:1769-1781`), while resume republishes `run.pid` before it writes the new `Running` snapshot (`src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:1820-1827`). Two concurrent `run resume`/`run stop` attempts against the same stale snapshot can therefore race so that the loser observes the winner's intermediate `Failed` snapshot and deletes the winner's freshly written pid file, after which `run status` and later recovery misclassify a live orchestrator as stale.","dedup_key":"77dfce7ff94a33f475db328d01763f9794c020bfa5620790d226d77096d69d32","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260410054251","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":61,"timestamp":"2026-04-10T07:38:09.214670749Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-3-36a3f606","body":"`src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:6470-6476` and `src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:6500-6593` only fall back to `snapshot.interrupted_run` when the journal has no `run_started` event at all. If the journal contains an older visible `run_started`/terminal pair, `run resume` binds to that old run id and cursor instead of the recovered snapshot metadata. A recovered stale-start snapshot can then fail with `all stages in the current flow are already complete` or resume the wrong run. I reproduced this by seeding `run.json` with `interrupted_run.run_id = run-current` and a journal containing an older `run_started`/`run_completed` for `run-old`; `ralph-burning run resume` exited with the bogus `already complete` error instead of resuming `run-current`.","dedup_key":"745c4f273a9aeb704cbd8bb653309ce3dc5481ae5e81dbd3af78e437ad399123","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260410054251","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
